comments: Anderson (MIN) maintains his right hand on the side of the ball during his dribble.
Niang (PHI) momentarily brings an arm to Russell's (MIN) left arm before correcting, and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Embiid (PHI) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Milton (PHI) initiates incidental hand on ball contact with Russell's (MIN) right hand during the drive.
Gobert (MIN) and Embiid (PHI) pursue the loose ball, and marginal arm contact with Embiid occurs during the rebound.
Gobert (MIN) is retreating alongside Embiid's (PHI) path and marginal body contact occurs during the drive.
Anderson (MIN) makes clean contact with ball during Embiid's (PHI) driving shot attempt.
Anderson (MIN) gathers the ball on two feet, then steps with his right, establishing his left foot as his pivot. He then lifts his left foot and switches his pivot to his right foot when he turns.
Embiid (PHI) brings his left arm down and initiates contact with Edwards' (MIN) right elbow, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Gobert (MIN) and Tucker (PHI) engage and disengage during the rebound, and marginal contact with Gobert's right arm occurs.
Russell (MIN) brings his arm toward Niang's (PHI) path and marginal contact occurs during the pick.
Anderson (MIN) brings his arm toward Melton's (PHI) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Melton (PHI) establishes his right foot as his pivot and maintains it.
Milton (PHI) gathers the pass on his right foot and takes three steps before releasing his dribble.
Edwards (MIN) exits the paint within three seconds.
Towns (MIN) steps towards Milton (PHI) and marginal body contact occurs as Milton gathers during his driving shot attempt.
Milton (PHI) brings his arm toward Russell's (MIN) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Milton (PHI) legally contests Russell's (MIN) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Melton (PHI) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Edwards (MIN) during the drive.
Edwards (MIN) briefly places a hand on Melton's (PHI) back and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Towns (MIN) brings a slight hand on Milton's (PHI) back as they pursue the loose ball and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Niang (PHI) commits a take foul on Towns (MIN) after he releases the pass. The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Milton (PHI) commits a take foul on Edwards (MIN).
On both free throws, Edwards (MIN) steps over the plane of the free throw line before the ball touches the basket ring, backboard or the free throw ends.
